<section class="hero">

<h1>
Gen<span>omics</span>
</h1>

<p>
Genomics investigates the complete set of genetic information encoded within DNA. Through sequencing, variant discovery, computational biology, and systems-level analysis, genomics enables precision medicine, disease discovery, and biological understanding across individuals and populations.
</p>

<div class="hero-image">
  <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
    <source src="/genomics-encoded biological information.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
</div>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
What is <span>Genomics?</span>
</h2>

<div class="infographic">

  <img
    src="/2_Genomics.png"
    alt="Genomics overview infographic"
  >

</div>

<p>
Genomics is the study of genomes, the complete DNA content of an organism. It examines genes, regulatory regions, genetic variation, genome structure, and how inherited or acquired changes influence biological function and disease.
</p>

<p>
Modern genomics combines sequencing technologies, computational analysis, population-scale datasets, and biological interpretation to understand health, disease, evolution, and precision medicine.
</p>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
Applications in <span>Research & Medicine</span>
</h2>

<div class="applications">

<a href="/research/genomics/whole-genome-sequencing" class="card">
  <img src="/whole-genome-sequencing.png" alt="Whole Genome Sequencing">

  <h3>Whole Genome Sequencing</h3>

  <p>
    Comprehensive sequencing of the entire genome, including coding and non-coding
    regions, to capture the broadest view of genetic variation.
  </p>
</a>

<a href="/research/genomics/whole-exome-sequencing" class="card">
  <img src="/whole-exome-sequencing.png" alt="Whole Exome Sequencing">

  <h3>Whole Exome Sequencing</h3>

  <p>
    Targeted sequencing of protein-coding regions to identify variants linked to
    inherited disease, rare disorders, and clinical diagnosis.
  </p>
</a>

<a href="/research/genomics/variant-discovery" class="card">
  <img src="/variant-discovery.png" alt="Variant Discovery and Interpretation">

  <h3>Variant Discovery & Interpretation</h3>

  <p>
    Identifying and interpreting genetic variants that influence biological
    function, disease risk, and therapeutic response.
  </p>
</a>

<a href="/research/genomics/single-cell-genomics" class="card">
  <img src="/single-cell-genomics.png" alt="Single-cell Genomics">

  <h3>Single-cell Genomics</h3>

  <p>
    Analyzing genomic variation at single-cell resolution to reveal mosaicism,
    clonal evolution, and cellular heterogeneity.
  </p>
</a>

</div>
</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
Genomics and <span>Omics Sciences</span>
</h2>

<p>
Genomics provides the foundational layer of omics sciences by defining the inherited and acquired DNA information that shapes biological systems. When combined with transcriptomics, epigenomics, proteomics, metabolomics, lipidomics, and microbiomics, genomics helps explain how molecular information becomes biological function.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, genomics is part of a broader systems-level framework for understanding life, disease, biotechnology, and precision health.
</p>

